WORSE FROM WITNESS The usual weekday began at the zoo. There were no fauna lovers yet, and the animals aimed marafet so that it could be seen how happy they were behind bars. - So that I once again ... - heard the monkey Zina behind her back and, looking around, saw her girlfriend the monkey Klava. -What happened? the monkey Zina asked cautiously. "Nothing good," the friend snorted. -And detail. - Yesterday I learned on my own head what grief from the mind is. -And what is it? - I foolishly took the pose of "Thinker" yesterday. So, the visitors mistook me for a person and stopped throwing bananas at me.